'''Toyoyuki Shrine''' (とよゆけじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ihara-chō|1=UNKNOWN}}, {{ill|lt=Shimizu-ku|Q79385|WD=Q79385|1=Shimizu-ku, Shizuoka}}, {{ill|lt=Shizuoka|Q174691|WD=Q174691|1=Shizuoka (city)}}, {{ill|lt=Shizuoka Prefecture|Q131320|WD=Q131320|1=Shizuoka Prefecture}}. Its former rank in the {{ill|lt=Modern shrine ranking system|Q712534|WD=Q712534|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}} was {{ill|lt=gōsha|Q134917316|WD=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}.

=== Outline ===
The founding is unknown. It stands directly south of the {{ill|lt=Ihara|Q988501|WD=Q988501|lt=Ihara|1=Ihara District, Shizuoka}} {{ill|lt=kofun group|Q11411019|WD=Q11411019|1=Kofun cluster}}.

In {{ill|lt=2005|Q2019|WD=Q2019|1=2005}} ({{ill|lt=Heisei|Q234510|WD=Q234510|1=Heisei era}} 17), construction of {{ill|lt=Shizuoka City Shimizu Ihara Ballpark|Q11662968|WD=Q11662968|1=Shizuoka City Shimizu Ihara Ballpark}} caused the loss of much of the kofun group, but shrine rites continue. It is also an old shrine connected with the {{ill|lt=Ihara clan|Q11486229|WD=Q11486229|lt=Ihara no Kuni no Miyatsuko|1=Ihara no Kuni no Miyatsuko}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{ill|lt=Toyouke-hime|Q2983724|WD=Q2983724|lt=Toyouke-hime-no-Mikoto|1=Toyouke-hime}} (main deity)
* {{ill|lt=Konohanasakuya-hime|Q1781862|WD=Q1781862|lt=Konohana-sakuya-hime-no-Mikoto|1=Konohanasakuya-hime}}

=== Precinct ===
In {{ill|lt=1858|Q7684|WD=Q7684|1=1858}} ({{ill|lt=Ansei|Q1327259|WD=Q1327259|1=Ansei}} 5), a landslide buried the shrine buildings.

In {{ill|lt=1872|Q7753|WD=Q7753|1=1872}} ({{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} 5), it was rebuilt. The shrine architecture shows similarities with {{ill|lt=Shizuoka Sengen Shrine|Q500368|WD=Q500368|1=Shizuoka Sengen Shrine}}. It is {{ill|lt=nagare-zukuri|Q210684|WD=Q210684|1=Nagare-zukuri}} with copper roofing.

The {{ill|lt=sessha|Q1071160|WD=Q1071160|lt=subsidiary shrine|1=Setsumatsusha}} Shinmei-gū follows the style of {{ill|lt=Toyouke Daijingū|Q11633343|WD=Q11633343|lt=Gekū|1=Toyōke Daijingū}}. It is a small shrine enshrining seven deities of {{ill|lt=Kōtaijingū|Q11581011|WD=Q11581011|lt=Naikū|1=Kōtai Jingū}} and {{ill|lt=Toyouke Daijingū|Q11633343|WD=Q11633343|lt=Gekū|1=Toyōke Daijingū}}.

=== Sessha and massha ===
===Precinct shrines===

* Shinmei-gū - {{ill|lt=Amaterasu|Q455602|WD=Q455602|1=Amaterasu}} (main deity) and others
* 14 shrines (enshrined separately by deity)

===Outer precinct shrine===

* Munakata Shrine - {{ill|lt=Ichikishima-hime|Q11059454|WD=Q11059454|lt=Ichikishima-hime-no-Mikoto|1=Ichikishima-hime}} / ancestral mausoleum of the {{ill|lt=Ihara clan|Q11486229|WD=Q11486229|1=Ihara clan}} (parallel to main hall)

